6.","meanings":["Dutch: occupational name for a cobbler.","Slovenian: nickname for a talkative person, from <i>lapati</i> ‘to babble’, or a topographic name from dialect <i>lap</i> ‘abyss’. Compare   Lapp   4."],"variants":[{"name":"Lapp","meanings":["German, English, and Dutch: from Middle High German and Middle English <i>lappe</i>, Middle Dutch <i>lap</i> ‘cloth, patch, rag’, a metonymic occupational name for a mender of clothes or shoes, or a nickname given to someone who wore ragged clothes or garments with loose folds, flaps, or hanging sleeves, or who had fleshy folds of skin on his face, neck, or body.","German: nickname for a simple-minded person, from Middle Low German <i>lappe</i> ‘fool’. This surname (in any of the two possible senses; see also 1 above) is also found in France (mainly Alsace, also Lorraine).","English: nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>lappe</i> ‘burdock’, perhaps for someone with a prickly character."]}]},{"name":"Trahaearn","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: composed of the intensive prefix <i>tra-</i> + <i>haearn</i> ‘iron’."],"variants":[{"name":"Traherne","meanings":["Traditional: composed of the intensive prefix <i>tra-</i> + <i>haearn</i> ‘iron’."]}]},{"name":"Foel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, composed of two different Hebrew elements, <i>Yah(weh)</i> and <i>El</i>, both of which mean ‘God’ the implication of the name is that the Hebrew God, <i>Yahweh</i>, is the only true god. This is a common name in the Bible, being borne by, among others, one of King David's ‘mighty men’ (1 Chronicles 11:38), and a minor prophet who lived in the 8th century  bc . The name has been perennially popular as a Jewish name; it was also taken up by the Puritans and other Christian fundamentalists. The name has long been in regular use in North America but was uncommon in Britain until the 1990s. Well-known bearers of the name include the American singer and entertainer  Joel Grey  (  b. 1932 ), the West Indian cricketer  Joel Garner  (  b. 1952 ), and the American film director  Joel Coen  (  b. 1954 ). The French form  <b>Joël</b>  is also used in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Trahaearn Foel Ap Maredudd was born about 1185, in Wales, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Trahaearn Foel ap Maredudd."},"et":{"about 1185–":"umbes 1185–Surnud","1176–Male":"1176–Surnud","1212–Male":"1212–Surnud","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","ABT    1212":"umbes 1212","1212":"1212","1176":"1176","1185":"1185","about 1185":"umbes 1185","of Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Llanybyther, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llanybyther, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1185–":"noin 1185–Kuollut","1176–Male":"1176–Kuollut","1212–Male":"1212–Kuollut","1185–Female":"1185–Kuollut","ABT    1212":"noin 1212","1212":"1212","1176":"1176","1185":"1185","about 1185":"noin 1185","of Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Llanybyther, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llanybyther, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1185–":"environ 1185–Décédée","1176–Male":"1176–Décédé","1212–Male":"1212–Décédé","1185–Female":"1185–Décédée","ABT    1212":"environ 1212","1212":"1212","1176":"1176","1185":"1185","about 1185":"environ 1185","of Wales":"Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Llanybyther, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llanybyther, Carmarthenshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Mrs Trahaearn Foel Ap Maredudd est née environ 1185, à Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Trahaearn Foel ap Maredudd."},"de":{"about 1185–":"um 1185–Verstorben","1176–Male":"1176–Verstorben","1212–Male":"1212–Verstorben","1185–Female":"1185–Verstorben","ABT    1212":"um 1212","1212":"1212","1176":"1176","1185":"1185","about 1185":"um 1185","of Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Llanybyther, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llanybyther, Carmarthenshire